# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
just assume we are standing on the last index
Aim: to somehow reach 0th index as **if we can reach last to zero we can reach zero to last index also**

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1.just maintain a (last_pos) variable that **keeps a track of your last position** you were able to travell from last index.

2.if current position(i) + value of current position(nums[i]) is grater then our last position(last_pos) that means we can reach to our last position(last_pos) from our current(i) position

3.And now if ***i + nums[i] >= curr_pos our curr_pos becomes i*** this means we can travell till i from the last index or we can successfully travell to last index from that position(i).

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
as we are iterating every element only once time complexity is O(n);

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
we have just used 2 extra variables n and last_pos that is constant which makes tc = O(1)

