Using the input array itself to keep track of the available jump at current index (memoization):
- If the previous index has 0, then there's no way to reach the current index, so update current index to eqaul to 0.
- Else we can make at least one jump from previous index, store the max jump available at current index.
- Lastly check the 2nd to last index(right before the target) should has available jump >= 1 else it can't jump one more to reach the end


```
class Solution:
    def canJump(self, nums: List[int]) -> bool:
        if len(nums) == 1:
            return True

        for i in range(1, len(nums)-1):
            if nums[i-1] == 0:
                nums[i] = 0
            else:
                nums[i] = max(nums[i-1]-1, nums[i])


        return nums[-2] >= 1
```

