<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
### Greedy TO(n) SO(1)
Maintain a reachable variable and update it on every iteration, if we are ahead of reachable that means it's not possible. else reachle will be equal to n

### DP TO(n^2) SO(n)
Using a 1d array to mark evry reachable destination by True and then check if we reached on then end or not.


### Recurssive TO(n^n) SO(1)
Try running DFS on every possible value and check if reached in the end or not.



