# Intuition
The idea is to continuously improve the position we can jump to.

Initially, we  can think of jumping to all available `k` position from each index where `k = nums[i]`, because we want to find the best reach from any index.

Instead of doing that we can simply pass all the elements in nums and see what is the furthest reach any of them places us at. If we step on an index we can't reach because the previous elements don't allow us to get there, then we exist by returning `false`. Otherwise we greedily update the best index we can reach until we can reach the end of the array.

The code is super simple and readable.


# Code
```
class Solution {
    public boolean canJump(int[] nums) {
        int n = nums.length;
        int maxReach = nums[0];

        for (int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
            if (i > maxReach) return false;
            maxReach = Math.max(i + nums[i], maxReach);
        }
        return true;

    }
}
```

