# Intuition


# Approach
Edge case: check if first element itself is 0 that means it can not take a move further and size of nums is greater than 1----> in this case return false

store first element of the array in a variable jump=nums[0];

after that iterate over a loop and decrement jump by -1 and check jump is lesser than the current value if so then assign jump to the current value;

in case if jump becomes 0 and you have not reached at the end point then return false

if false statement doesn't execute then true statemnt automatically will be executed just after completion of the loop

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(nums.size())---->as we are only iterating through a loop of vector nums


- Space complexity:
O(1)--->constant space there is no auxillary space as we are not using any othe data structure

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool canJump(vector<int>& nums) {
        int i=1,n=nums.size(),jump=nums[0];
        if(jump==0&&n!=1) return false;
        while(i<n){
            jump--;
            if(nums[i]>jump)
            jump=nums[i];
            if(jump==0&&i!=n-1)
            return false;
            i++;
        }
        return true;
    }
};
```

